'''Al-Hashmi Al-Hussain Mohialdin''' ({{langx|ar|الهاشمي الحسين محي الدين}}; born 15 August 2003) is a Qatari professional [[association football|football]]er who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] club [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi]] and the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Club career==
Al-Hussain started his career at [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi SC]] in Qatar. In 2023, he was loaned to [[CD Calahorra B|Calahorra B]] in the Spanish [[Tercera Federación]], before being loaned out to [[AD Alcorcón B|Alcorcón B]] the following season.<ref name="worldfootball"/>

Following the end of his loan at Alcorcón B, he returned to Al-Arabi.<ref>{{cite web |title=Al-Arabi SC Announces Return of Al Hashemi Al Hussein, Salem Reda after End of Their Loan Spells in Spain |url=https://qna.org.qa/en/news/news-details?id=al-arabi-sc-announces-return-of-al-hashemi-al-hussein-salem-reda-after-end-of-their-loan-spells-in-spain&date=4/07/2025 |website=Qatar News Agency |access-date=26 May 2026 |date=4 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Al-Hussain represented [[Qatar national under-20 football team|Qatar's under-20 national team]] at the [[2023 AFC U-20 Asian Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |title=QFA announces squad for Under-20 AFC Asian Cup |url=https://www.gulf-times.com/article/652248/sport/qfa-announces-squad-for-under-20-afc-asian-cup |website=Gulf Times |access-date=26 May 2026 |language=en |date=27 December 2022}}</ref> playing in all three matches as they were eliminated in the group stage.<ref name="worldfootball"/> He also played for [[Qatar national under-23 football team|Qatar's under-23 national team]] at both the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup|2024]] and [[2026 AFC U-23 Asian Cup|2026]] [[AFC U-23 Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AFC-U23-Asian-Cup-Qatar-2024™---Squad-Lists-(Updated-April-11).pdf |url=https://assets.the-afc.com/2024_AFC_U23_Asian_Cup/Downloads/Squad_List/AFC-U23-Asian-Cup-Qatar-2024™---Squad-Lists-(Updated-April-11).pdf |access-date=26 May 2026 |date=11 April 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Qatar squad named for AFC U-23 Asian Cup |url=https://www.olympic.qa/media-center/qatar-squad-named-afc-u-23-asian-cup |website=www.olympic.qa |access-date=26 May 2026 |language=en |date=3 January 2026}}</ref>

He made his international debut for the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]] on 11 June 2024, in a 2–1 win against [[India national football team|India]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|second round of 2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]], where he assisted [[Yousef Aymen]]'s controversial goal in the 73rd minute.<ref>{{cite web |title=Qatar vs India: AFC World Cup Qualifiers |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/ceqqw872dgxt |website=BBC Sport |access-date=26 May 2026 |date=11 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Eltayeb |first1=Mohamed |title=Controversial goal dashes India's World Cup qualifying hopes, sparks calls for probe |url=https://dohanews.co/controversial-goal-dashes-indias-world-cup-qualifying-hopes-sparks-calls-for-investigation/ |website=Doha News |access-date=26 May 2026 |date=12 June 2024}}</ref> He also represented Qatar at the [[26th Arabian Gulf Cup]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Qatar name 26-player squad for Arabian Gulf Cup |url=https://thepeninsulaqatar.com/article/19/12/2024/qatar-name-26-player-squad-for-arabian-gulf-cup |website=thepeninsulaqatar.com |access-date=26 May 2026 |language=en |date=19 December 2024}}</ref> and the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Lopetegui Finalizes 23-Man Squad for FIFA Arab Cup |url=https://www.qfa.qa/en/news/lopetegui-finalizes-23-man-squad-for-fifa-arab-cup |website=QATAR FOOTBALL ASSOCIATION |access-date=26 May 2026 |language=en |date=24 November 2025}}</ref> where Qatar finished last in their group both times.

On 12 May 2026, Al-Hussain was included in Qatar's 34-man preliminary squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |title=National Team Preliminary List Released for World Cup 2026 |url=https://www.qfa.qa/en/news/national-team-preliminary-list-released-for-world-cup-2026 |website=[[Qatar Football Association]] |access-date=25 May 2026 |language=en |date=12 May 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Qatar announce preliminary squad |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/qatar-announce-preliminary-squad |website=www.fifa.com |access-date=26 May 2026 |date=13 May 2026}}</ref> and remained part of the squad when it was trimmed down to 28 players on 25 May, prior to a [[exhibition match|friendly]] against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web |title=28 لاعباً في قائمة العنابي لمباراة أيرلندا الودية الدولية |url=https://www.qfa.qa/ar/news/28-لاعباً-في-قائمة-العنابي-لمباراة-أيرلندا-الودية-الدولية |website=الاتحاد القطري لكرة القدم |access-date=26 May 2026 |language=ar |date=25 May 2026}}</ref> He was officially included in their final squad on 1 June.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Qatar Football Association |author-link=Qatar Football Association |user=QFA_EN |number=2061519863403741405 |date=June 1, 2026 |title=The official squad for the FIFA World Cup 2026™ has been announced. |access-date=June 2, 2026}}</ref>

